        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "wraps-per-inch",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpd4lxy50000ukv4dcdvz1rc"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " reading gives the spinner a single number that maps straight to a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "yarn weight category",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdw8fmn0000ckv4z5m4p51b"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". WPI is measured in inches because the standard tables are set in inches. The reading itself is taken from a 1-inch (2.5 cm) section of a ruler. The number is just a count, no unit on it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How to measure WPI",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hold the yarn in the non-dominant hand without tension (do not stretch it). Wrap it around a ruler or a dedicated WPI tool at a measured 1-inch section. Each wrap should touch the previous without overlapping or gapping. Count the wraps. Repeat twice and average the three readings.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "WPI to yarn weight table",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
